</td></tr></tbody></table>
<table width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" role=
=3D"presentation" style=3D"mso-table-lspace:0pt;mso-table-rspace:0pt;word-b=
reak:break-word;"><tbody><tr><td class=3D"r" style=3D"padding-bottom:32px;"=
><div style=3D"color:#000000;direction:ltr;font-family:&#39;Inter&#39;,&#39=
;Arial&#39;;font-size:17px;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:0px;line-height:1=
50%;text-align:left;mso-line-height-alt:25.5px;"><p style=3D"margin:0;margi=
n-bottom:0px;"><strong><em>John Ourand</em></strong><strong>:</strong> <str=
ong>You have peace
with the union. You set an attendance record last year. Your championship g=
ame set a viewership record. As the commissioner of the NWSL, where will yo=
ur focus be?</strong></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p=
><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><em>Jessica Berman</em>: One area=
 where we are laser focused is on transcending cultural relevance to ensure=
 that more people know the amazing stories of our athletes and the teams. C=
reating cultural relevance and
discoverability through storytelling is our primary focus on the fan side. =
We spent a lot of time last season learning about our audience, and figurin=
g out who the addressable audience is. What you=E2=80=99re now going to see=
 is partnerships that are specifically, and intentionally, going after the =
audience segment that we know and believe, based on our data and research, =
would be most interested in the NWSL.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-=
bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">
One of the ways we=E2=80=99re doing that is through original content. We la=
unched our first ever docuseries on Amazon Prime on March 6. It=E2=80=99s c=
alled <em>For the Win</em>, and it followed our eight playoff teams from th=
e quarterfinals to the semifinals to the final.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin=
:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><=
strong>I=E2=80=99ve seen that in practice. As you know, I live in the D.C. =
market, where the Washington Spirit=E2=80=99s Trinity Rodman is probably be=
tter known
than any D.C. United player or Washington Mystics player.=C2=A0</strong></p=
><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;ma=
rgin-bottom:0px;">She=E2=80=99s a perfect example, because she tells her st=
ory in a really authentic way in the docuseries. She=E2=80=99s also putting=
 herself out there more, with our encouragement. She was on <strong>Alex</s=
trong> <strong>Cooper</strong>=E2=80=99s <em>Call Her Daddy</em> podcast, w=
here millions of people had the chance to hear her story. Trinity is a huge
unlock to the casual fan.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=
=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><strong>What are other leag=
ues doing well?</strong></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0=
</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">The NHL 4 Nations Face-Off was=
 something I really paid attention to. It was interesting to see the way pe=
ople were so interested in getting behind their nationalities and the count=
ries that are represented in the league. There=E2=80=99s a lot of
analogies to what we have in our league, such as the way the NHL has repres=
entation globally=E2=80=94it doesn=E2=80=99t only have American athletes. P=
art of what made that interesting was that there was real competition from =
other countries.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</=
p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><strong>What could the NWSL lear=
n from that?=C2=A0</strong></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=
=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">At its base level, it
reinforces what we already know, which is that people really care about the=
 national tournaments. And, of course, soccer is like the ultimate proof ca=
se with the World Cup and the Olympics. It=E2=80=99s the question of how yo=
u create, market, and scale an event like the 4 Nations Face-Off. More impo=
rtantly for the NHL, the challenge becomes taking that excitement and bring=
ing it back into the regular season. For example, our league couldn=E2=80=
=99t have had a more successful Olympics in 2024. We worked really
hard to bring that tailwind into our league.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin=
-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><strong>Di=
d you feel that tailwind? Because hockey does great in the Olympics, but th=
e NHL generally doesn=E2=80=99t see an uptick in TV viewership afterward. O=
lympic basketball was great, but the NBA saw their early-season viewership =
actually drop significantly.</strong></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom=
:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">You have
to define the metrics you=E2=80=99re looking for. There may or may not be a=
 tailwind that=E2=80=99s directly tied to the next week, or the next month.=
 But it is fair to say that we experienced positive indicators around the s=
uccess of the Olympics, and players like the Triple Espresso trio of Sophia=
 Smith, Mallory Swanson, and Trinity Rodman.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin=
-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;">It=E2=80=99s easy to identif=
y the low-hanging fruit that you=E2=80=99re looking for, like TV ratings or
attendance. And of course those are important. To the extent that happens, =
it=E2=80=99s great. But it=E2=80=99s also important to look at some of the =
other things that you might see.</p></div>
